<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>av</supplied>y<supplied>a</supplied>yam</w><pc>•</pc><w>tsopats</w><w>cämplam</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ṣāñatsum</w><pc><supplied>•</supplied></pc><w><supplied>pari</supplied>pūrṇa<supplied>m</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ta</supplied>nn<supplied>e</supplied></w><w>w<supplied>e</supplied>wñu</w><pc>•</pc><w>pr<supplied>atiṣev</supplied>y<supplied>aṃ</supplied></w><w>vip<supplied>aryayāt</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>y<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><pc>•</pc><w>tavānekāṃśavādina<supplied>ḥ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ṣo</supplied>ma-kälyme</w><w>träṅkäntāñ</w><num value="29">20<supplied>-9</supplied></num><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>205-208</citedRange></bibl></note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>wram</hi>: translates <hi>°artham</hi> in 6.25a <hi>anvartham</hi> 'der Bedeutung entsprechend' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>205</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>tsopats cämplam</hi>: translates 6.25d <hi>mahāsāmārthyam</hi> in <hi>ekāntamahāsāmārthyam</hi> 'von ganz und gar gewaltiger Kraft' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>205</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>ṣāñatsum</hi>: translates 6.26b <hi>upāyavat</hi> 'heilvolle Mittel besitzend' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>206</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment"><hi>(ta)nn(e) w(e)wñu</hi>: translates 6.28c <hi>ity uktaṃ</hi> 'so ist (von dir) gesagt' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>207</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>/// y·</hi>: this is the end of the translation of 6.29a <hi>°sevāyāṃ</hi> 'in service' in <hi>iṣṭāniṣṭasevāyāṃ</hi> 'die Pflege des Erwünschten und des Unerwünschten' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>208</citedRange></bibl>). <bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1966"/><citedRange>176</citedRange></bibl> suggests to restore <hi>(paṃ yāmlune)y(aṃ)</hi> 'in serving'.</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment"><hi>(ṣo)ma-kälyme träṅkäntāñ</hi>: translates 6.29d <hi>ekāṃśavādinaḥ</hi> 'die (nur) einseitig lehren' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:hartmannju1987"/><citedRange>208</citedRange></bibl>).</note></p>
         </div>
